article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 37, McNeese St. 17
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Brady Attaway threw for 248 yards and a touchdown and Stephen F. Austin came back to beat McNeese State 37-17 on Saturday. McNeese State took a 17-7 lead in the first minute of the second quarter after Cody Stroud's 2-yard TD pass to Harold Turnage. But the Lumberjacks (3-5, 2-2 Southland) roared back and scored the game's last 30 points. Attaway's 9-yard pass to Cordell Roberson gave Stephen F. Austin a 23-17 lead in the third quarter. The Lumberjacks added two more touchdowns on Will Jefferson's interception in the end zone and Fred Ford's 1-yard run. Jeremy Barnes finished with 68 yards rushing and a TD for Stephen F. Austin and Jordan Wiggs kicked three field goals. Stroud threw for 198 yards and Champlain Babin ran for a 5-yard score for the Cowboys (3-5, 2-3), who have lost four straight.
